creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of First World War Centenary Poetry Collection. Read in English by David Wales; Ruth Golding; John Hayward; Winston Tharp; Lucy Perry; Kara Shallenberg; Ernst Pattynama; Martin Geeson; MaryAnn; Phil Schempf; Patrick Wallace; Son of the Exiles; ravenotation; Lynne Thompson; filespnr; Sieska; Kasper; alanmapstone; SkyAlbatross; J Korth. Read in Dutch by Anna Simon. Read in French by Patrick Wallace; Ruth Golding. Read in German by Hokuspokus; Julia Niedermaier; Patrick Wallace; Ruth Golding. Read in Portuguese by Leni. Read in Russian by Anastasiia Solokha. This collection of poetry, with its companion prose collection, commemorates the outbreak of the First World War on 28th July 1914. Most of the poetry, all chosen by the readers, is in English, but the collection also includes poems in Dutch, French, German, Portuguese and Russian. Please note that some poems are still protected by copyright in countries which observe copyright laws based on the author's date of death. The majority of the poems were written during the war itself, but some poems have been included for their relevance in other ways. For more information about each poem, please see this document (PDF format), which also shows the poets' dates of death. (Summary by Ruth Golding) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
